*juk-3.5_alpha1 (07 Sep 2005)

  07 Sep 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> +juk-3.5_alpha1.ebuild:
  Added 3.5_alpha1 split ebuild.

  08 Aug 2005; Bryan Østergaard <kloeri@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.2.ebuild:
  ~alpha keyword.

  29 Jul 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.2.ebuild:
  Use local use flag musicbrainz to determine whether to build musicbrainz
  support (defaulting to off). This matches the new kdemultimedia ebuild
  usage. musicbrainz has been a problematic dep, historically.

*juk-3.4.2 (28 Jul 2005)

  28 Jul 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org>
  +files/configure-fix-kdemultimedia-juk.patch, +juk-3.4.2.ebuild:
  Version bump to 3.4.2.

  08 Jul 2005; Jason Wever <weeve@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.1.ebuild:
  Stable on SPARC.

  02 Jul 2005; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.1.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc; Bug #97544.

  01 Jul 2005; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.1.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc64 (bug #97544)

  26 May 2005; Gregorio Guidi <greg_g@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.1.ebuild:
  Change flag 'oggvorbis' into 'vorbis' (#89592), 'mad' into 'mp3' (#94045).

*juk-3.4.1 (25 May 2005)

  25 May 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> +juk-3.4.1.ebuild:
  Ebuilds for KDE 3.4.1. These are package.masked until 3.4.1 is actually
  released. You can't get the tarballs yet.

  27 Apr 2005; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.0.ebuild:
  Added ~ppc64 to KEYWORDS

  26 Mar 2005; Jason Wever <weeve@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.0.ebuild:
  Added ~sparc keyword.

  18 Mar 2005; Daniel Goller <morfic@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.0.ebuild:
  Added to ~ppc

  14 Mar 2005; Marcus D. Hanwell <cryos@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.0.ebuild:
  Marked ~amd64, keywording KDE split ebuilds, bug 80944.

  13 Mar 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.0.ebuild:
  KDE 3.4.0 ebuilds. Note that the tarballs won't be officially released for a
  few more days.

*juk-3.4.0_rc1 (27 Feb 2005)

  27 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> +juk-3.4.0_rc1.ebuild:
  Ebuild for 3.4.0 RC1.

  07 Feb 2005; Simone Gotti <motaboy@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.0_beta2.ebuild:
  Now juk has a fixed dep on akode, so it needs its libs and its headers.

*juk-3.4.0_beta2 (05 Feb 2005)

  05 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> +juk-3.4.0_beta2.ebuild:
  Ebuild for 3.4.0_beta2. Note that beta2 has NOT been released as of this
  date. This ebuild is for inside testing by the KDE team, and is of course
  package.masked.

  17 Jan 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> juk-3.4.0_beta1.ebuild:
  Add missing (optional) dep on gstreamer and gst-plugins.

*juk-3.4.0_beta1 (15 Jan 2005)

  15 Jan 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> +juk-3.4.0_beta1.ebuild:
  Adding the split ebuilds to portage. For KDE 3.4, we've created separate
  ebuilds for all the KDE apps.

